01:21.164 --> 01:23.538
Hey, listen to this
wedding announcement:

01:23.709 --> 01:25.916
"Laird Prescott
to marry Annabelle Saberhagen."

01:26.753 --> 01:27.953
Is she any relation to you?

01:28.130 --> 01:31.416
Me? Why, no, of course not--

01:31.592 --> 01:32.755
[SOBBING]

01:32.926 --> 01:34.125
She's my daughter.

01:34.344 --> 01:36.089
Daughter? You have a daughter?

01:38.891 --> 01:40.137
Salem has a daughter?

01:40.309 --> 01:41.555
He's 500 years old.

01:41.768 --> 01:43.809
He didn't spend all that time
watching television.

01:44.980 --> 01:47.306
Annabelle hasn't been in touch
with him for decades.

01:47.482 --> 01:50.853
It's caused him many sleepless nights,
which is why he sleeps all day.

01:51.069 --> 01:53.692
It's their family, their rift.
We leave it alone.

01:53.864 --> 01:55.739
And that's coming from me,
a real busybody.

01:55.949 --> 01:58.322
Salem has a daughter?

01:58.952 --> 02:00.697
I know it's personal
and I don't wanna pry,

02:00.871 --> 02:02.532
so I won't ask any questions.

02:02.706 --> 02:04.332
Thank you.

02:04.499 --> 02:07.751
Annabelle blames me for being away
so much when she was growing up.

02:07.920 --> 02:10.412
Is that because you were away
so much when she was growing up?

02:10.589 --> 02:14.339
Yeah, but collapsing governments
isn't something you can do from home.

02:14.510 --> 02:16.420
I'm finding it hard
to be impartial here,

02:16.637 --> 02:18.926
but there's so little you've done right.

02:19.097 --> 02:21.850
- Why didn't you ever call?
- I'm too guilty to call.

02:22.017 --> 02:25.304
And then when I was found guilty,
I really felt too guilty to call.

02:26.104 --> 02:29.142
But I still love my little pumpkin.

02:29.316 --> 02:31.025
[SOBBING]

02:31.235 --> 02:32.694
Is there anything I can do to help?

02:32.861 --> 02:34.819
Just spitballing, but...

02:36.198 --> 02:39.899
So let me get this straight.
My father is your house pet?

02:40.118 --> 02:41.911
A very contrite house pet.

02:42.079 --> 02:43.408
And he loves you very much

02:43.580 --> 02:45.490
and he desperately wants to share
your wedding with you.

02:45.666 --> 02:47.790
[SOBBING]

02:47.960 --> 02:49.918
He does?

02:51.296 --> 02:52.922
You've certainly got
your father's cry.

02:53.090 --> 02:54.918
I always wanted him
to be in my wedding,

02:55.092 --> 02:56.670
I just wanted him to ask.

02:56.885 --> 02:58.262
Well, I'm asking for him.

02:58.428 --> 03:00.303
Close enough.

03:01.723 --> 03:03.516
Oh, I'm sorry.
I'm just so overwhelmed.

03:03.684 --> 03:05.428
There's so much
to planning a wedding.

03:05.644 --> 03:06.724
I could help.

03:06.895 --> 03:09.565
I could fold napkins
or handle the guest book, park cars.

03:09.773 --> 03:11.149
Would you be my maid of honour?

03:11.733 --> 03:13.478
Oh, as if we know each other.

03:13.694 --> 03:16.268
Who better to share my special day
than the person responsible

03:16.446 --> 03:18.820
for mending the rift
between my daddy and me?

03:19.575 --> 03:21.319
Other than a sister
or a college roommate

03:21.493 --> 03:24.365
or a lifelong friend,
I can't think of anyone.

03:24.580 --> 03:25.909
[SOBBING]

03:26.081 --> 03:27.245
Thank you.

03:27.833 --> 03:29.873
- Hey.
- Guess what this is.

03:30.043 --> 03:32.203
You have a shop full
of unhappy customers.

03:32.421 --> 03:33.667
No, it's bread.

03:34.298 --> 03:37.715
It's from that bakery that we both loved
so much back in the 17th century.

03:37.885 --> 03:39.594
Have a bite.

03:40.262 --> 03:43.134
Mm. Mm.

03:43.390 --> 03:46.226
Where did you get this?
I thought we cleaned out the freezer.

03:46.435 --> 03:48.761
I found the instruction manual
to the lost-in-time clock.

03:48.937 --> 03:51.097
And I was so bored,
I actually read it.

03:51.273 --> 03:53.314
Check out all the great things
this clock can do.

03:53.483 --> 03:55.643
Been able to make it tell time yet?

03:55.819 --> 03:58.394
Not yet, but it can answer
questions about history,

03:58.572 --> 04:00.447
which I don't care about,
but you will.

04:00.616 --> 04:03.285
And it can bring back anything
you want from any year you want.

04:03.452 --> 04:05.659
And it's a salad spinner.

04:05.829 --> 04:07.372
Go ahead, play with the clock.

04:07.539 --> 04:10.114
Well, shouldn't we be out there
helping the customers?

04:10.334 --> 04:12.908
Oh, they'll go away. They always do.

04:13.128 --> 04:16.415
SALEM: I can't believe my little girl
has finally forgiven me.

04:16.632 --> 04:19.634
From here on in, whatever
pumpkin wants, pumpkin gets.

04:19.843 --> 04:22.513
And she wants you to perform
the duties of father of the bride.

04:22.679 --> 04:24.139
Are you nuts?

04:24.348 --> 04:27.385
I just wanted to go and watch it
from the back like Stella Dallas.

04:27.601 --> 04:29.891
I can't do father-of-the-bride stuff.
I'm a cat.

04:30.062 --> 04:32.221
You can write a cheque
and walk her down the aisle.

04:32.397 --> 04:34.438
Well, what will I do
on the father-daughter dance?

04:34.608 --> 04:36.068
Ride on her shoe?

04:36.693 --> 04:38.070
And I can't--

04:38.237 --> 04:40.989
Hey, would you be my second

04:41.198 --> 04:44.200
and perform any duties
I'm too furry to do?

04:44.409 --> 04:46.984
Maid of honour,
backup father of the bride.

04:47.162 --> 04:49.405
Fine, but I draw the line at catering.

04:49.915 --> 04:52.537
I'm so glad
you two patched everything up.

04:52.751 --> 04:54.994
Me too. We need dates.

04:55.212 --> 04:56.292
Oh, good heavens, yes.

04:56.463 --> 04:58.089
We can't go unescorted
to a wedding.

04:58.298 --> 05:00.873
They'll try to fix us up
with every loser in the place.

05:01.093 --> 05:02.885
You can hook up
with my uncle Morty.

05:03.095 --> 05:05.801
You mean,
Uncle Inappropriate Behaviour?

05:05.973 --> 05:07.551
Well, I wish I could take Willard.

05:07.766 --> 05:10.435
But fortunately,
it's in the Other Realm, so you can't.

05:10.602 --> 05:12.181
This looks like a job
for Mystery Date.

05:12.396 --> 05:14.436
- What?
- Another feature of our little clock.

05:15.649 --> 05:18.568
All we have to do is state which
qualities we want in our mystery date,

05:18.735 --> 05:20.563
and then spin the hands
of the clock.

05:21.154 --> 05:24.607
I'd like someone
who is independent, adventurous

05:24.783 --> 05:26.860
and likes long walks on the beach.

05:28.996 --> 05:30.325
[CLOCK CHIMES]

05:34.168 --> 05:35.544
Leif Ericson?

05:35.752 --> 05:39.253
You forgot to say,
"But who isn't a Viking."

05:39.756 --> 05:43.376
I don't wanna pick, but maybe it's time
for you to clean out your locker.

05:44.803 --> 05:45.883
They're bridal magazines.

05:46.054 --> 05:48.131
Somehow I got roped
into helping plan a wedding.

05:48.307 --> 05:51.474
I was talking
about the old sandwiches.

05:55.272 --> 05:57.266
Sabrina and I share lockers.

05:57.441 --> 05:58.936
It's kind of like living together.

05:59.610 --> 06:01.769
I'm all gooey inside.

06:05.616 --> 06:08.108
Looks like Sabrina's planning
a wedding.

06:08.285 --> 06:10.077
I wonder whose.

06:10.245 --> 06:11.871
If the tux fits, buddy.

06:12.039 --> 06:14.328
That doesn't sound like Sabrina.

06:14.499 --> 06:15.580
We're going to college.

06:15.751 --> 06:17.127
I'm driving the Indy 500.

06:17.294 --> 06:19.086
No way she's thinking
about marriage.

06:19.254 --> 06:20.833
That's what my brother thought.

06:21.006 --> 06:22.834
Now he's got three kids.

06:28.889 --> 06:30.301
Copernicus may have realised

06:30.474 --> 06:32.551
that the Earth
isn't the centre of the universe,

06:32.768 --> 06:34.678
but he hasn't realised that he isn't.

06:35.979 --> 06:38.187
- I'm going to spin again.
- No, it's my turn.

06:38.398 --> 06:40.024
You've already sent back 16 guys.

06:40.234 --> 06:42.358
Go through your maybe pile again.

06:42.528 --> 06:46.858
Well, Leif is smelling better
now that he's dry.

06:48.075 --> 06:50.365
I want someone
who'll take out the garbage.

06:50.536 --> 06:52.613
In other words, the outdoorsy type.

06:57.668 --> 06:59.957
- Davy Crockett?
- I'm Daniel Boone.

07:00.170 --> 07:01.452
Excuse me. Heh.

07:03.298 --> 07:06.918
I think the real Davy Crockett
would be a little less touchy.

07:08.512 --> 07:09.841
Josh.

07:10.055 --> 07:13.258
If you're gonna drool over Sabrina,
do it over the spill tray.

07:13.433 --> 07:16.934
Ah-- I do not like Sabrina.

07:19.231 --> 07:21.308
Hey, Harvey's here.
Can I take my break now?

07:21.483 --> 07:23.607
Just finish wiping the counter.

07:23.777 --> 07:26.316
If you think your love
can wait that long.

07:26.530 --> 07:29.104
I'm just gonna go up to her
and ask her about the magazines.

07:29.283 --> 07:32.238
That's a good idea. I think
it's about time you two had the talk.

07:32.452 --> 07:33.698
The talk?

07:37.249 --> 07:38.744
Yeah, you bring this up
with Sabrina

07:38.917 --> 07:41.789
and you're gonna have talk to her
about whether you wanna marry her.

07:41.962 --> 07:43.374
Which you don't.

07:47.467 --> 07:48.749
That's gonna upset her.

07:48.927 --> 07:50.387
She's gonna break up with you.

07:50.554 --> 07:53.472
And then you can go to motocross
with me on Saturday night.

07:57.227 --> 07:59.137
I gotta go think.

08:00.731 --> 08:03.223
How about I take two breaks later?

08:04.151 --> 08:05.480
You know
what's wrong with women?

08:05.986 --> 08:07.185
I'm dying to know.

08:07.404 --> 08:08.568
They keep yanking that leash

08:08.739 --> 08:10.898
until the poor dog turns around
and bites.

08:11.116 --> 08:12.659
I'll embroider that on a pillow.

08:15.245 --> 08:16.954
Do you wanna hear
what I just heard?

08:17.164 --> 08:19.288
You know, Marnie,
you're nothing but a gossipmonger.

08:19.458 --> 08:23.159
- It's about Sabrina and Harvey.
- I don't care if it's about Sabrina and--

08:23.337 --> 08:24.880
Tell me later.

08:25.506 --> 08:27.583
[HUMMING]

08:30.636 --> 08:33.839
SALEM:
Let's check the fifth at Aqueduct.

08:34.556 --> 08:36.135
[THUNDER CRASHES]

08:39.061 --> 08:40.472
[SIGHS]

08:41.188 --> 08:43.145
Daddy?

08:43.315 --> 08:44.561
Your daughter's here.

08:44.775 --> 08:45.855
Oh, no.

08:46.026 --> 08:49.147
I've waited 50 years to see her
and she picks now?

08:49.363 --> 08:54.405
Oh, why did I choose today to sample
the new Mexican Science Diet? Oh.

08:54.618 --> 08:56.908
Daddy, where are you?

08:57.120 --> 08:58.829
SALEM:
Be right there.

08:59.998 --> 09:02.241
[HUMS THEN CLEARS THROAT]

09:04.086 --> 09:05.961
Oh, Daddy.

09:06.171 --> 09:07.203
SALEM:
Pumpkin.

09:07.381 --> 09:08.876
[SALEM SOBBING]

09:09.049 --> 09:10.628
I missed you, my precious little girl.

09:10.801 --> 09:12.213
Me too.

09:12.386 --> 09:16.135
Oh, is that sand on your paws?

09:17.391 --> 09:19.799
Hey, I thought Harvey
was coming back, but since he hasn't,

09:19.977 --> 09:22.646
can I take my two breaks plus one
from tomorrow and leave now?

09:22.855 --> 09:24.848
Oh, man, I hate word problems.

09:25.065 --> 09:26.726
Here's a hint. The answer's yes.

09:26.942 --> 09:28.651
Go.

09:32.406 --> 09:35.692
Now, what exactly did you hear
about Harvey and Sabrina?

09:35.909 --> 09:38.532
It sounded like
they might be breaking up.

09:38.745 --> 09:42.080
Apparently, Harvey won't be standing
in the way of destiny anymore.

09:42.666 --> 09:43.865
Okay, good.

09:44.042 --> 09:46.001
Because I am not letting Sabrina
get away again.

09:46.170 --> 09:48.543
The next time I see her,
I'm asking her out.

09:48.755 --> 09:51.082
Oh, I forgot my backpack.

09:52.134 --> 09:54.009
That didn't count.

10:00.225 --> 10:02.552
What do you think about this
for my bouquet?

10:02.728 --> 10:03.808
Bouquet?

10:03.979 --> 10:06.269
- At a wedding?
- What am I missing here?

10:06.481 --> 10:09.685
At an Other Realm wedding,
the maid of honour carries a sapling.

10:09.902 --> 10:12.061
- You mean a tree?
- Just a small one.

10:12.237 --> 10:13.863
And it's planted in a sacred grove.

10:14.031 --> 10:16.902
And every year,
the couple visits it on their anniversary.

10:17.117 --> 10:18.281
Oh, that's kind of sweet.

10:18.493 --> 10:21.661
Not surprisingly,
a popular wedding gift is manure.

10:22.539 --> 10:24.996
Okay, but it doesn't get
any weirder than that, right?

10:29.671 --> 10:31.831
Are you sure
I'm supposed to be wearing this?

10:32.007 --> 10:34.499
SALEM: I might have dyed the boots
to match the dress.

10:34.718 --> 10:37.293
Yep, that's the traditional
maid-of-honour outfit.

10:37.513 --> 10:39.340
Don't you guys ever question
these traditions?

10:39.515 --> 10:41.804
It's been traditional not to.

10:43.185 --> 10:44.680
SABRINA:
Hey, it's Davy Crockett.

10:44.895 --> 10:47.054
- Daniel Boone.
- Sorry.

10:47.272 --> 10:49.396
Good Lord, Sabrina,
you're the maid of honour?

10:49.608 --> 10:53.441
So? Other than looking like a before
picture, it doesn't seem that hard.

10:53.654 --> 10:54.734
Oh, that's right.

10:54.905 --> 10:56.982
You've never been
to an Other Realm wedding before.

10:57.157 --> 10:59.483
Well, good luck.

10:59.952 --> 11:01.661
This way.

11:11.338 --> 11:13.166
- Are they bunny-hopping?
- Of course.

11:13.340 --> 11:17.006
It symbolises the importance
of whimsy in a lasting relationship.

11:17.219 --> 11:18.679
[SHEEP BLEATING]

11:18.846 --> 11:21.385
- And what do the sheep symbolise?
- Nothing.

11:21.557 --> 11:23.634
Apparently,
this place is close to a ranch.

11:24.685 --> 11:26.429
I'm ready.

11:26.603 --> 11:31.065
Wow. I want to say something wise
and wonderful right now,

11:31.608 --> 11:35.144
but I can't think of anything,
except I love you

11:35.320 --> 11:36.780
[CRYING]
and I hope the band knows

11:36.947 --> 11:38.228
some Ohio Players.

11:39.241 --> 11:42.029
Oh, look, there's my beloved Laird
waiting for me.

11:42.953 --> 11:45.990
Isn't it amazing how all men
look great in a suit of armour?

11:46.206 --> 11:47.536
[ORCHESTRAL MUSIC PLAYING]

11:47.749 --> 11:48.830
This is the kind of music

11:49.001 --> 11:51.244
that Brian Boitano wears
the dark skates for.

11:51.461 --> 11:53.585
It's the Other Realm
wedding march.

11:53.797 --> 11:56.336
Time to start down the aisle.

11:56.884 --> 11:59.043
So where's the sapling
I'm supposed to carry?

11:59.261 --> 12:01.302
Behind you.

12:03.098 --> 12:05.056
The bigger the tree,
the greater the love.

12:08.353 --> 12:10.810
Couldn't you have married
for money?

12:11.023 --> 12:14.108
Thanks for letting me practise what
I'm gonna to say to Sabrina on you.

12:14.276 --> 12:16.234
No problem.

12:16.403 --> 12:18.729
You don't really think
she'll start weeping and shouting,

12:18.906 --> 12:21.694
"Dear heavens, this is gonna change
everything forever,"

12:21.867 --> 12:23.196
like you did, do you?

12:25.412 --> 12:27.489
[ORCHESTRAL MUSIC PLAYING]

12:29.458 --> 12:30.538
[SABRINA GRUNTS]

12:30.709 --> 12:34.922
Put some shoulder in it, Sabrina.
You're holding up the whole wedding.

12:36.423 --> 12:39.211
Hey, Jim,
did you bring your Bowie knife?

12:39.384 --> 12:41.343
It's Daniel.

12:43.555 --> 12:46.890
The wedding ceremony
is important for all of us

12:47.100 --> 12:48.975
because it includes
ancient traditions--

12:49.144 --> 12:50.604
[PANTING AND WHEEZING]

12:55.108 --> 13:01.230
Ancient traditions that remind us
of the sacred sanctity of marriage.

13:02.032 --> 13:04.571
Let's blow up the balloon.

13:06.537 --> 13:07.783
You gotta be kidding me.

13:07.996 --> 13:10.239
The maid of honour
always blows up the balloon.

13:13.460 --> 13:15.833
The inflated balloon symbolises...

13:17.005 --> 13:20.625
Ahem.
The inflated balloon

13:20.801 --> 13:22.960
symbolises that a couple needs--

13:23.136 --> 13:24.336
[BALLOON DEFLATING]

13:25.764 --> 13:29.383
- Ugh.
- Sabrina, you can use magic.

13:33.230 --> 13:35.307
You could have used magic
to bring the tree in too,

13:35.482 --> 13:37.191
but guess it's too late
to tell you that.

13:37.401 --> 13:40.568
The inflated balloon symbolises

13:40.737 --> 13:44.107
that a couple needs to love
each other with every breath.

13:45.492 --> 13:47.533
Please tell me that's all I have to do.

13:47.703 --> 13:48.783
Pretty much.

13:48.954 --> 13:54.329
And now for the most sacred moment
of the wedding ceremony, the ring.

13:54.543 --> 13:56.335
I don't have it. I didn't bring a ring.

13:59.756 --> 14:00.837
That's the ring.

14:01.049 --> 14:05.179
The father of the bride will now wrestle
the father of the groom

14:05.345 --> 14:09.047
for the right of his daughter
to marry his son.

14:09.266 --> 14:11.010
Okay, now the wedding's
just getting weird.

14:11.185 --> 14:13.759
- Don't worry, you can take him.
- Me?

14:13.979 --> 14:18.025
You're my second, and I'm protected
by the Humane Society.

14:18.233 --> 14:20.476
Sabrina, please fight for me.

14:20.652 --> 14:22.231
If you don't win, I can't marry Laird.

14:22.404 --> 14:24.528
And I just can't imagine life
without Laird.

14:24.698 --> 14:25.944
[SOBBING]

14:29.661 --> 14:31.322
But you can imagine life
without me?

14:36.668 --> 14:38.461
What's up, Kinkle?

14:38.629 --> 14:41.963
As soon as Sabrina gets in,
I'm gonna have the talk with her.

14:42.174 --> 14:45.544
Really?
I mean, well, good luck, man.

14:48.680 --> 14:51.517
There goes another dog
who's about to shed his leash.

14:54.478 --> 14:58.311
According to my sources,
the breakup is imminent.

14:58.482 --> 15:00.606
If I understand my dog analogies.

15:01.151 --> 15:02.481
Thanks for the info.

15:02.653 --> 15:04.196
Now why don't you
get back to work?

15:05.614 --> 15:08.616
That's code for:
Why don't you get back to work?

15:09.952 --> 15:11.447
Ladies and gentlemen.

15:11.620 --> 15:12.652
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

15:12.829 --> 15:18.205
In this corner,
weighting 267 pounds,

15:18.418 --> 15:24.505
the father of the groom,
Xavier "The Avenger" Prescott.

15:24.675 --> 15:26.668
[LOUDER CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

15:26.885 --> 15:29.175
This part of weddings
always gets me.

15:29.388 --> 15:32.390
And in this corner, at 110,

15:32.599 --> 15:37.595
Sabrina
"Hasn't Got a Nickname" Spellman.

15:37.813 --> 15:40.103
[CHEERS AND BOOS]

15:40.274 --> 15:42.730
- What do I do?
- Go for his weak point.

15:42.943 --> 15:44.319
Which is where?

15:50.492 --> 15:53.660
[SABRINA SCREAMS
THEN GRUNTS]

15:53.829 --> 15:55.324
[SCREAMS]

15:58.542 --> 16:01.081
Don't let him pin you
or the match is over.

16:02.421 --> 16:03.750
[CHEERS AND BOOS]

16:06.300 --> 16:08.839
Go, Sabrina. Kick him.

16:09.344 --> 16:10.508
Gouge his eyes.

16:10.721 --> 16:12.513
Really. This is a wedding.

16:16.977 --> 16:18.472
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

16:25.194 --> 16:30.070
[SABRINA GRUNTS, SCREAMS]

16:32.367 --> 16:35.286
You know, whoever catches
the wrestler gets married next.

16:35.495 --> 16:37.288
Next wedding,
I'm just sending a gift.

16:37.497 --> 16:39.290
Sabrina, your slip is showing.

16:47.841 --> 16:49.123
SALEM:
This isn't right.

16:49.343 --> 16:53.258
I can't just sit here and watch
while poor Annabelle loses her love.

16:53.722 --> 16:55.763
Not to mention
Sabrina getting filleted.

16:55.974 --> 16:58.098
Annabelle, I'm going in the ring.

16:58.310 --> 17:00.802
I'm so glad I spent three hours
doing my hair.

17:01.230 --> 17:05.063
[SALEM WHIMPERING]

17:05.233 --> 17:07.108
SALEM:
Saved by Daniel Boone.

17:07.319 --> 17:09.692
It's Daniel Boone!

17:10.113 --> 17:11.395
Sorry.

17:11.615 --> 17:13.027
SALEM:
No.

17:13.242 --> 17:15.319
[SALEM GRUNTING, WHIMPERING]

17:18.872 --> 17:21.115
One, two, three.

17:21.333 --> 17:22.365
[BELL RINGS]

17:22.542 --> 17:23.824
The winner.

17:27.881 --> 17:30.551
Please stay down.

17:30.717 --> 17:31.999
I'm glad you won.

17:32.177 --> 17:37.848
With my other son, I got beat up
and I've got gypsies as relatives.

17:39.852 --> 17:44.431
And now for the exchanging
of the ring fingers.

17:48.360 --> 17:50.852
Oh, gross, gross, gross.

17:51.071 --> 17:53.740
You are now part
of each other forever.

17:53.949 --> 17:56.655
I declare you husband and wife.

17:56.827 --> 17:58.287
You may kiss the bride.

17:58.495 --> 18:00.868
Finally, a tradition I've heard of.

18:01.415 --> 18:03.658
Aren't you gonna kiss me?

18:05.586 --> 18:06.701
[APPLAUSE]

18:06.879 --> 18:10.165
[SOBBING]
It's beautiful, just beautiful.

18:10.382 --> 18:13.004
Okay, it's all right.

18:13.218 --> 18:17.169
Well, I dropped Sabrina off at work
and sent Leif back to Greenland.

18:17.347 --> 18:19.839
You did send Daniel back,
didn't you?

18:20.058 --> 18:21.719
Hey, it's a rule.

18:21.935 --> 18:23.893
What is that vile odour?

18:25.063 --> 18:27.223
It's possum pie. The real stuff.

18:27.399 --> 18:28.811
- Not with Ritz crackers.
- Ugh!

18:29.026 --> 18:31.482
I think you might have gotten
some glands in there.

18:33.238 --> 18:35.031
There's my pie.

18:35.199 --> 18:37.607
So we already have nicknames?

18:38.660 --> 18:41.117
Thank you, darling. Mm.

18:41.288 --> 18:46.366
Well, I have to send you back,
so I finally picked a date.

18:46.543 --> 18:48.204
How about the 12th of never?

18:53.675 --> 18:54.756
What are you doing here?

18:54.968 --> 18:56.214
After Harvey talks to Sabrina,

18:56.386 --> 18:59.388
he's gonna need someone around
to pick up the pieces.

19:01.517 --> 19:04.435
After Harvey talks to Sabrina,
you might wanna pick up the pieces.

19:04.645 --> 19:05.760
Check.

19:05.938 --> 19:08.940
If all goes well, you and I
will have nothing more to talk about.

19:12.444 --> 19:14.105
Kinkle.

19:14.988 --> 19:16.863
Good luck, man.

19:18.325 --> 19:19.951
Thanks.

19:20.327 --> 19:21.443
[DISHES CLINK]

19:21.620 --> 19:24.112
- Hey.
- Hey, so, what's ticking, chicken?

19:25.499 --> 19:26.875
I'll never say that again.

19:28.210 --> 19:30.749
Sabrina, I love you.

19:31.547 --> 19:33.955
Really?
Even after "What's ticking, chicken?"

19:34.508 --> 19:35.884
[CHUCKLES]

19:36.552 --> 19:38.213
I bought you this.

19:42.099 --> 19:43.843
A ring?

19:44.017 --> 19:46.344
Harvey, does this mean
what I think it means?

19:46.520 --> 19:48.312
Probably not.

19:48.480 --> 19:51.482
See, I don't wanna get married.
I'm not ready.

19:52.025 --> 19:53.141
Good, neither am I.

19:54.236 --> 19:55.316
You're not?

19:55.487 --> 19:58.988
Of course not, I'm still in high school.
I have my whole life ahead of me.

19:59.157 --> 20:01.484
I'm not ready to have someone
carry a tree down an aisle.

20:01.702 --> 20:04.905
- A tree?
- Yeah, my dad's kind of wooden.

20:05.080 --> 20:06.741
Wait, but I'm confused.

20:06.915 --> 20:09.703
Why did you give me a ring
if you don't wanna marry me?

20:09.877 --> 20:11.336
It's a promise ring.

20:11.503 --> 20:14.339
It's to let you know that someday,
a long time from now,

20:14.506 --> 20:18.007
if we haven't grown apart
or joined some strange religious cult,

20:19.261 --> 20:23.342
only if you want to, of course,
I hope that maybe we will get married.

20:23.557 --> 20:25.182
That's so sweet.

20:25.350 --> 20:28.139
And, Harvey Kinkle, I accept
your proposal to not get married.

20:30.105 --> 20:31.648
What happened?

20:31.815 --> 20:32.931
What happened?

20:33.108 --> 20:34.224
Who knows?

20:38.197 --> 20:40.356
Hey, guys, look what Har--

20:40.574 --> 20:43.991
I swear, no one in this place
even knows I'm alive.

20:48.707 --> 20:51.495
Aunt Hilda, I thought Dan
was going back to Kentucky

20:51.668 --> 20:52.867
of yesteryear.

20:53.086 --> 20:55.376
Don't tell your Aunt Zelda,
but he's gonna stay a while.

20:55.547 --> 20:58.253
Apparently, he wants to court me.
I'm game.

20:58.467 --> 21:00.544
You brought him down here
to embarrass me?

21:00.761 --> 21:02.090
And the house smells like possum.

21:02.638 --> 21:05.426
Are you supposed to be
Davy Crockett?

21:05.933 --> 21:08.259
Fine. I'm Davy freaking Crockett.

21:08.435 --> 21:11.307
That's right, all those guys
in buckskin jackets look the same.

21:11.522 --> 21:15.223
Honey, I think
it might be the coonskin hat.

21:15.400 --> 21:17.892
Oh, they do have a point.

21:18.737 --> 21:20.232
Remember the Alamo.

